      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on an embedded c++ project for a vehicle control unit and i'm hitting a wall. we're seeing a slow memory leak where the heap keeps shrinking over about a 4-6 hour window. i've checked the main loops but cant find any obvious missing deletes. can you give me a systematic way to track down where the allocation is failing to free up? here is the core telemetry loop where i suspect it might be happening:\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data(SensorData* data) {\n    if (data != nullptr) {\n        LogEntry* entry = new LogEntry(data->timestamp, data->value);\n        buffer.push_back(entry);\n        \n        if (buffer.size() > MAX_BUFFER_SIZE) {\n            // something happens here but i cant tell if it's clearing right\n            process_buffer(); \n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
